Use default reference config values for manual calibrate listed on the website. 
keep delta radius the same as it was before. just the raise height / offset won't be in use with this method. (the nozzle is the probe) 



enables the use of klipper screen zoffset button to run delta calibrate manual paper method. just use it as normal hitting accept will move to the next point
once done exit the menue and, hit save config from the tft. 


[gcode_macro Z_ENDSTOP_CALIBRATE] #klipperscreen workaround to run delta calibrate on klipper screen. 
#rename_existing: DELTA_CALIBRATE_MANUAL 
description: run klipper screen zoffset menu as delta calibrate manual instead. 
gcode: 
  G28
  G91
  G1 Z-50 F1500
  G90
  G28
  G91
  G1 Z-50 F1500
  G90
  G28
  G91
  G1 Z-50 F1500
  G90
  G28
  G91
  G1 Z-50 F1500
  G90
  G28
  G91
  G1 Z-50 F1500
  G90
  G28
  ENDSTOP_PHASE_CALIBRATE stepper=stepper_a
  ENDSTOP_PHASE_CALIBRATE stepper=stepper_b
  ENDSTOP_PHASE_CALIBRATE stepper=stepper_c
  BED_MESH_CLEAR 
  DELTA_CALIBRATE METHOD=manual
